@node Introduction

2. Introduction
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Font2src creates an assembly source file of any font.

All fonts (I believe) that comes with the Workbench disks
shows a not particularly interesting rectangle for
characters in the range 0x00-0x1F and 0x80-0x9F.

Font2src has an option for mapping these characters to the
inverse of 0x40-$5F and 0xC0-$DF respectively.

This was an option in my program TextView, but it only
worked with 8x8 fonts. I removed it and created this
program instead. Now the font dimension is not a limit, and
other programs can benefit as well.

Font2src was created by looking at the RKRM example font
suits8. You can get it from:
· Aminet: dev/misc/RKRM_Lib2.lha 
                   (Graphics_Libraries/Text/Suits8.asm)
· Fish disk: 742 (RKRM_Lib2) or 344 (RKMCompanion)


