@node Usage

4. Usage
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Font2src must be stared from the CLI/Shell, it cannot be
used from Workbench.

The AmigaDOS template is:
NAME/A,SIZE/A/N,SAVE/S,INV/S,TAB/S,LF/S:

Usage example:
Font2src NAME topaz SIZE 8 SAVE INV

NAME and SIZE are always required parameters. The option INV
is the idea with this program (see Introduction). SAVE will
create the source file. It will be saved in the current
directory without any warning. In this example it would have
the name "topaz8.s". If you don't specify SAVE, you will get
some information about the font instead.

TAB and LF will will initialize TAB (0x09) as a thin
vertical line, and LF (0x0A) as a triangle.


@endnode
@node Source

5. Source
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
So, what do we do with the source?

· Change font name declared at "fontName:".
  For example, change "topaz" to "topazx".

· Assemble. No include files are needed. A68k/Blink can be
  used from Fish disk 571 and 40 or Aminet:
  dev/asm/a68k271.lzh and dev/misc/blink67.lzh
  Example to be typed at the CLI prompt:
      a68k topaz8.s
      Blink topaz8.o

· Copy the font to FONTS:.
  Example:
      MakeDir FONTS:topazx
      Copy topaz8 FONTS:topazx/8

· Create a font contents file (continuing the example, it
  would be FONTS:topazx.font).
  This can be done automatically with FixFonts, which should
  be in your System drawer.
  Example:
      Sys:System/FixFonts


